{"id":37447,"date":"2021-11-29T10:09:02","date_gmt":"2021-11-29T06:09:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=37447"},"modified":"2021-11-29T10:09:02","modified_gmt":"2021-11-29T06:09:02","slug":"angels-ask-muhammad","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/29\/angels-ask-muhammad\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Graves: Angels come to ask about Muhammad"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When the servant is placed in his grave, his companions turn and leave until he hears the scuffing of their sandals. Two angels come to him and sit by his head, saying to him: What do you say about this man, Muhammad? He says: I testify that he is the servant of Allah and His Messenger. It will be said: Look at your seat in Hellfire, for Allah has replaced it with a seat in Paradise. He will see them both together. As for the unbeliever or hypocrite, he says: I do not know, as I only said what people said! It will be said: You did not know, nor did you recite! Then he will be struck between his two ears with an iron hammer and he will cry out such that whoever is near him will hear it except humans and jinn.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1338, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2870<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/em><\/strong> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u200c\u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e <strong>\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\